nitrogenous fluids (water not included); and we have seen that not one of these was in the least affected. We may therefore safely conclude that in the sixty\_
four experiments with nitrogenous fluids the inflection of the exterior tentacles was due to the absorption of 
\par [page 82]
\par nitrogenous matter by the glands of the tentacles on the disc. 
