\par }{\i\fs24\insrsid6359192 Polypompholyx multifida}{\fs24\insrsid6359192 .--The bladders are attached in whorls round the summits of stif
f stalks. The two antennae are represented by a minute membranous fork, the basal part of which forms a sort of hood over the orifice. This hood expands into two wings on each side of the bladder. A third wing or crest appears to be formed by the extensio
n
